text: Behren-Bokel Transmitter. The Behren-Bokel Transmitter, also known as the Sprakensehl Transmitter is a 323-metre high guyed steel tube radio mast in Behren-Bokel near Uelzen in Lower Saxony, Germany. The mast is used for FM- and TV-broadcasting, and was at its erection time in 1961 the highest construction of West Germany. ==See also== * List of masts ==External links== * * http://skyscraperpage.com/diagrams/?b46676 Category:Radio masts and towers in Germany Category:Towers completed in 1961 Category:1961 establishments in Germany
